Angry villagers in the eastern Nigerian state of Anambra have set a church ablaze after its pastor conducted a wedding between a man and his teenager sister, the Nigerian Tribune has reported. The local community in Agba, Ekwulobia, termed the union as an abomination. ALSO READ:

PCEA church to sell land to clear Sh0.5b loan The report says the siblings' older brother conducted the wedding, citing Biblical scriptures to back up his actions.